1
00:01:25,700 --> 00:01:29,980
=The Youth Memories=

2
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:32,980
=Episode 17=

3
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:34,640
To make some money,

4
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:36,160
I can sell my charms

5
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:37,360
and commit myself to her.

6
00:01:38,160 --> 00:01:39,200
It's a sacrifice but I'm fine.

7
00:01:39,440 --> 00:01:41,360
You? Commit yourself?

8
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:43,040
You don't even know if she wants you.

9
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:44,640
There it is. It's open.

10
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:48,320
Leave me alone!

11
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:49,240
Go!

12
00:01:49,620 --> 00:01:51,860
(Trade Fair Month of
Winter Clothing, Shoes and Hats)

13
00:01:57,600 --> 00:01:58,960
Come and see!

14
00:01:58,960 --> 00:02:00,800
- Come and have a look.
- Woolen scarves.

15
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:02,360
Madam, do you want a scarf?

16
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:03,520
Come on.

17
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:04,280
Have a look.

18
00:02:04,280 --> 00:02:05,800
Newly arrived woolen scarves.

19
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:06,240
This one.

20
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:07,280
Excuse me,

21
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:08,880
how much is your scarf?

22
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:11,030
Not expensive, only ten yuan each.

23
00:02:11,030 --> 00:02:11,800
Ten yuan?

24
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:12,440
Ten yuan each.

25
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:15,000
It'd only cost
six or seven yuan in the store.

26
00:02:15,160 --> 00:02:17,240
It's cheaper in the store indeed,

27
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:18,360
but it's hard to get one there.

28
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:19,920
What he said is right.

29
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:22,040
It's hard to get
woolen scarves like this.

30
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:23,760
It's out of stock in the store.

31
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:25,440
Look, what she said makes perfect sense.

32
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:26,080
Wise lady.

33
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:27,040
We have gone

34
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:28,520
through a lot

35
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:29,920
to find these scarves.

36
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:31,200
Okay, I'll buy one.

37
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:31,960
Sure!

38
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:33,400
I want two scarves.

39
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:34,840
- Sure.
- Thank you, madam.

40
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:35,960
I want one.

41
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:37,200
Sure.

42
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:38,000
Thank you.

43
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,320
Have a look. Our scarves will
make you youthful and happy,

44
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:42,400
and bring you good luck
in your friendship and career.

45
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:42,920
Come on.

46
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:43,960
Come on. This one.

47
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:44,840
Look at this one.

48
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:49,360
Xiaohui, how much money have we made?

49
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:51,840
Think about it.

50
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,720
We went to the Department Store

51
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:54,920
and bought 40 scarves.

52
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:56,640
The profit per scarf is three yuan.

53
00:02:57,160 --> 00:02:59,280
So we have earned 120 yuan.

54
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:01,880
120 yuan in only a few hours?

55
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:03,920
It's worth it to queue up at night.

56
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:04,800
We should keep doing this.

57
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:05,640
Heizi,

58
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,320
this is a lucrative business.

59
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,920
For sure.

60
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,280
Unfortunately,

61
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,960
we don't have this chance every day.

62
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:16,000
That's already good enough.

63
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:17,840
120 yuan

64
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:20,120
is about two months' wages of my father.

65
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:21,440
You should be happy.

66
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:25,800
Heizi, how do we divide the money?

67
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:29,720
Darling,

68
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:30,680
give it to me.

69
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:35,760
Cap-opener,

70
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:37,400
here's ten yuan for you.

71
00:03:38,480 --> 00:03:39,480
Buy a small gift

72
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:40,680
for your classmate,

73
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:42,520
I mean, that chubby girl.

74
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:45,040
Why should I buy a gift for her?

75
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:46,880
Boy, how ungrateful you are.

76
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:49,280
Do you still remember that
she did us a favor?

77
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:50,680
This classmate of yours

78
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:52,640
provided us with information

79
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:53,920
and saved some scarves for us.

80
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:55,320
You have to thank her.

81
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,360
As long as we remain friends,
we can get another chance like this again.

82
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:59,320
We can't make it a one-time deal.

83
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:00,360
Take it.

84
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:01,200
That makes sense.

85
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:02,200
- Take it.
- Hurry up.

86
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:02,920
Okay then.

87
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:04,240
I'll go to the store in Xidan

88
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,160
to buy her a brooch.

89
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:06,000
She likes brooches.

90
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:07,520
That's right.

91
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:10,640
Heizi, then what should we do
with the rest of the money?

92
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:13,680
We have 110 yuan left.

93
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:14,640
Well,

94
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:16,510
take ten yuan out of it first,

95
00:04:16,510 --> 00:04:18,950
then the rest 100 yuan will be
divided equally among us four.

96
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:20,240
However,

97
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:22,040
we can't spend the money now.

98
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:23,440
Why?

99
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:24,880
We're short of funds now.

100
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:26,840
We could only buy these 40 scarves

101
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:28,880
after saving money

102
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:30,400
in every possible way.

103
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:32,120
If we have more money,

104
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:33,200
then we can buy more

105
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:34,360
and earn more.

106
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:36,080
Heizi is right.

107
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:37,320
I agree.

108
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:38,040
Then

109
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:39,760
what about the ten yuan you took out?

110
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:42,240
The ten yuan I took out...

111
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:44,400
Let's eat out.

112
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:46,120
Okay.

113
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:46,880
How about that?

114
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:47,760
What should we eat?

115
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:48,800
What do you want to eat?

116
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:52,440
We haven't had
roasted duck for a long time.

117
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:55,080
Let's have roasted duck
near Hepingmen.

118
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:55,680
Okay.

119
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:56,200
Let's go.

120
00:04:56,200 --> 00:04:56,800
- Get on the tricycle.
- Let's go.

121
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:57,560
Go.

122
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:58,040
Come on.

123
00:04:58,440 --> 00:04:59,640
Let's go!

124
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:01,920
Ouch...

125
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:06,920
Bean sprouts and peanuts

126
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:08,160
taste worse than roasted duck indeed.

127
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:09,680
Of course they taste worse.

128
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:12,000
If you want to eat good food,
work hard.

129
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:13,840
Earn more money so you can
have roasted duck every day.

130
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:14,920
Okay.

131
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:16,160
Listen,

132
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:18,680
if you really want to
have roasted duck every day,

133
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,120
apart from working hard,

134
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:23,120
you have to figure out
ways to make money.

135
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:25,640
We have few ways to make money now.

136
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:27,760
Yeah.

137
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:29,760
Apart from woolen scarves,

138
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:32,160
we have to figure out

139
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:33,360
other profitable items we can sell.

140
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:37,360
By the way, Cap-opener left to see

141
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:39,040
that girl a long time ago

142
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:40,160
and he still hasn't returned.

143
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:41,960
Listen,

144
00:05:41,960 --> 00:05:43,760
they're quite close now.

145
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:46,040
Maybe he treated her to a big dinner.

146
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:47,880
I'm back!

147
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,240
Speak of the devil.

148
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:54,200
Come on, sit down.

149
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:56,680
How's it going?

150
00:05:57,120 --> 00:06:00,480
Did you have fun with that chubby girl?

151
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:02,160
Heizi,

152
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:03,400
you're awesome.

153
00:06:03,520 --> 00:06:04,840
Your idea is brilliant.

154
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:07,000
When I gave her the brooch,

155
00:06:07,280 --> 00:06:08,800
her eyes lit up.

156
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:10,520
Then I treated her

157
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:12,080
to steamed stuffed buns and liver fry.

158
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:12,920
Guess what?

159
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:15,640
She told me
another chance to make money.

160
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:16,680
What chance?

161
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:20,720
Say it now.

162
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:21,880
She told me

163
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:26,320
that military boots from Tianjin
are highly sought after now.

164
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:27,760
They often go to Tianjin

165
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:29,400
to purchase

166
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:31,640
and the boots

167
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:32,720
will be sold out in a minute.

168
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:35,640
Military boots.

169
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,120
I've seen them.

170
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:40,120
Those warm

171
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:41,080
ankle boots

172
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:42,840
made of calfskin. Right?

173
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:43,440
Yes.

174
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:45,640
Then ask her

175
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:47,120
when the store
will start selling the boots.

176
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:48,200
Save some for us.

177
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:49,360
She told me

178
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:51,400
not to purchase from the store.

179
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:53,120
The price there is higher.

180
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,920
If we want to purchase the boots,
we should go to Tianjin.

181
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:56,440
If we make a purchase in Tianjin

182
00:06:56,880 --> 00:06:58,120
other than from the store,

183
00:06:58,400 --> 00:07:00,400
then we can earn 5% more.

184
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,280
Tianjin?

185
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:03,560
Then we have to get there by train.

186
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:05,120
It's too far.

187
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:06,720
Don't worry.

188
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:08,560
Let's calculate it.

189
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:11,400
Now, a pair of military boots

190
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:14,000
will sell for about 26 or 27 yuan

191
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:15,200
in the store.

192
00:07:15,280 --> 00:07:16,320
We're not asking for too much profit.

193
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:18,480
Let's raise the price
by five yuan per pair.

194
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:20,640
If we purchase them in Tianjin,

195
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:23,680
then we can earn two or three yuan more.

196
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:25,920
So the profit will be eight yuan.

197
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:27,520
It takes about 20 yuan

198
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:29,360
for us four

199
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:31,040
to make a round trip

200
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:34,320
between Beijing and Tianjin.

201
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:37,680
This is profitable.

202
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:41,480
Yes, yes, it's profitable.

203
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:43,880
Then how about

204
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:44,880
you go there without me?

205
00:07:45,080 --> 00:07:46,080
It saves one train ticket.

206
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:49,240
Why do you have to save money now?

207
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:52,560
Do you know how heavy
a pair of military boots is?

208
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:54,760
If you go with us,
then we can carry more boots.

209
00:07:54,760 --> 00:07:56,200
The profit of one pair of boots

210
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:58,240
will be enough
to cover your train ticket cost.

211
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:00,680
Also,

212
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:04,120
we can visit Tianjin.

213
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:06,480
Let's try

214
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:07,520
that Goubuli steamed stuffed buns

215
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:09,440
and see what makes them

216
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:10,360
different from our ones.

217
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:12,440
The fried dough twists there
are also tasty.

218
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:14,040
And the ear-hole fried cakes too.

219
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:14,840
Yes!

220
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:15,280
Okay.

221
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:17,520
High-quality military boots.

222
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:20,040
Made of shiny calfskin.

223
00:08:20,280 --> 00:08:20,800
Size 37.

224
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,040
Size 37. Let me have a look.

225
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,520
Sir, what size do you wear?

226
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:24,880
Come on, this way!

227
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:28,080
Okay.

228
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:29,040
Come on.

229
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:30,920
Come and have a look!

230
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,120
Military boots!

231
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:33,910
These are all size 43 ones!

232
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:35,670
Yes, we have all sizes.

233
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:38,030
Choose the size you wear.

234
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,440
High-quality military boots!

235
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:50,680
It's so early.

236
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:52,000
Why did you ask me to go outside?

237
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:53,600
The weather is good

238
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:54,520
and you're having a day off.

239
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:56,360
I just wanted to take you outside.

240
00:08:56,680 --> 00:08:57,880
Where do you want to go?

241
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:00,040
Nowhere special. I'm just cycling around.

242
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:02,320
I just want to take you outside to relax.

243
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:18,720
Heizi, we're getting
fewer and fewer customers.

244
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:19,760
Of course.

245
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:21,520
Do you know what time it is?

246
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:23,040
It's not the time people get off work,

247
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:24,320
of course there won't be
many customers here.

248
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:24,880
Anyway,

249
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:26,640
we sold one third
of the boots in the morning.

250
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:27,240
That's good enough.

251
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:29,400
Then should we stay here?

252
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:33,360
I don't think we can sell more.

253
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:34,360
Let's go home.

254
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:35,400
Go home?

255
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,200
Do you have anything else planned?

256
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:40,720
Even if we go home,
we won't have much to do.

257
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:42,080
Let's just stay here.

258
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:43,680
More people will come here

259
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:44,400
when they get off work.

260
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:46,400
Maybe we can sell seven or eight pairs.

261
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:48,400
Okay, hang in there.

262
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:55,520
Hello, Xiaohui!

263
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:56,560
Hello, Yanqiu.

264
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:57,360
Tian!

265
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:58,400
Hello, Tian.

266
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,880
Tian, I haven't seen you for a long time.

267
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:00,800
I mean,

268
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,200
what brought you here today?

269
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:03,760
Nothing brought me here.

270
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:05,040
I cycled here.

271
00:10:05,320 --> 00:10:06,880
Tian, so you're not busy today.

272
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:08,800
Right. You're not busy today either.

273
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:10,400
I'm here to visit you.

274
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:11,320
Good.

275
00:10:12,040 --> 00:10:12,720
Xiaohui,

276
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:14,280
you're getting prettier and prettier now.

277
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:15,640
Look at your rosy cheeks.

278
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:18,320
Yanqiu, I'm afraid
I'm not getting prettier.

279
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:19,520
My face is red because of the cold.

280
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:23,400
Where did you get so many military boots?

281
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:24,640
We took an overnight train

282
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:26,680
to carry them back
from Tianjin Quanye Bazaar.

283
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,760
Why did you have to buy so many of them?

284
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:31,040
To earn money, of course.

